{"id":42157,"date":"2024-08-22T20:06:40","date_gmt":"2024-08-22T16:06:40","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=42157"},"modified":"2024-08-22T20:07:49","modified_gmt":"2024-08-22T16:07:49","slug":"signposts-islam","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2024\/08\/22\/signposts-islam\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Islam: Signposts on the Straight Path"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201c<strong>Verily, Islam has milestones, lamps like the lamps on the road. Among them are that you worship Allah without associating anything with Him, you perform the prayer, you give charity, you perform the Hajj pilgrimage to the House, you fast in the month of Ramadan, and you enjoin good and forbid evil. It is your greeting of peace when you enter your household and your greeting of peace to the children of Adam when you meet them. If they return it to you, the angels return it to them. If they do not return it, the angels return it to you, or curse them, or stay silent over them. Whoever belittles any of these, it is a sign of Islam he has abandoned. Whoever casts them all aside has thrown Islam behind his back.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad al-Sha\u0304miyyi\u0304n lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 429<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0644\u0650\u0644